# Keep this deployment out of search results for the duration of the rebuild.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠️  REMOVE THIS RULE AT DNS CUTOVER, or the live site will never index.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Why the rule is unscoped (`/*` rather than a workers.dev host match):
# `_headers` allows only ONE wildcard per rule, so `https://*.workers.dev/*`
# is invalid and gets silently skipped at build — that exact mistake left
# every path except `/` indexable on the previous deployment for a year.
# Until a custom domain is attached, workers.dev is the only way to reach
# this site, so an unscoped rule is both correct and unambiguous.
#
# This also fails in the safe direction: nothing can be indexed by accident,
# only by deliberately deleting these lines.
#
# NOTE: `_headers` applies to STATIC ASSETS ONLY. Responses generated by the
# Worker (any route with `prerender = false`) do not get this header and will
# need it set in middleware. There are no such routes today.
#
# At cutover, alongside deleting this: set `workers_dev: false` in
# wrangler.jsonc so no noindex'd duplicate of production is left standing,
# and point `site` in astro.config.mjs at https://christiangaetano.com.

/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex
